text:
i can‚Äôt do this alone. you probably can‚Äôt either. thank god we don‚Äôt have to. saturday, 5pm, let‚Äôs gather. gather our strength, gather our numbers, gather our love, gather our solidarity, gather our truths, gather our defiant hope.

this won‚Äôt be an evening where we share our trauma stories. it will be an evening where we look each other in the eyes with love, power and solidarity. it will be an evening of realizing we‚Äôre truly not in this alone, no matter how bad or scary it gets. it will be an evening of calling on our unbreakable spiritual centers to empower and nurture us, and allowing our feral human feelings to move through and cleanse us. 
for those of you new to me and my work: i am a trauma resolution educator, coach and guide. i have hosted dozens of workshops and retreats for survivors, and cultivate incredibly safe, non-triggering environments for alchemy and healing to happen. we will be using this gathering to orient towards health, allowing pain to move through, but with a focus on our individual and collective power. 
please tag friends who may be interested in attending.

you must dm to receive the address. i will do all my replies once a day, towards the evening, so if you don‚Äôt hear from me right away, don‚Äôt worry.

survivors of all genders, sexes, races, ages, sizes, classes and identities are welcome. the home is wheelchair accessible, the beach is not. non-survivors who stand in fierce solidarity are also welcome.

#metoo #survivorcircle #sandiego #onebillionrising #stopkavanaugh #rebloomtogether #blackfridays

text:
the truth about 'getting over' trauma. üî•
((i'm about to lay it down like you might have never heard it before because this conversation needs to be had.)) the biggest thing holding you back is that you're so easily knocked down, right? 
i mean, think about it - how easily are you triggered? how easily do you get knocked into unworthiness? how fast do you fall into fear the minute things don't go right?

how fast do you question your purpose or power to create your life - the minute you feel unseen, unheard, unsuccessful .... or argued with? 
usually - that comes from trauma. big or small, many or just a few painful wounds... it grooves itself into your cells, into your beliefs, into your vibrational memory. 
and? it changes how your brain functions to keep you safe!! no wonder you feel like everyone's out to get you or afraid of stepping out in faith! you're body - your cells - have learned that this is how it's done so you survive. 
they don't know how to thive. 
or trust. 
or believe you're capable. 
they're busy keeping your head above water. 
which is why you are busy keeping your head above water. 
your outer life parallels your inner pain and power. always. 
this is why a woman drowning in pain, feels powerless. you can't be in your power - when you're drowning in pain. 
so how do you not drown? 
oh, well... this is something i know. because you know i know trauma. so we're going to to go there. you ready? 
trauma is real. it‚Äôs all real. i‚Äôve said it, validated it, seen you, heard you and felt the pain with you, cause it‚Äôs my pain too. 
and one thing i‚Äôve learned from living trauma after trauma - is that seeing and hearing is a vital aspect. 
so we do that, right? we validate each other and hold each other up. we march, protest, write, sing, create - all in the name of calling shit out that we finally see and believe.

but.

calling all the shit out all the time is keeping you in it. 
i believe that balance is a myth in so many different situations - but this one? no. 
here‚Äôs the problem. 
one camp of people are screaming and shouting hear us, see us, know our pain.

another camp of people are screaming (continued üëá)

text:
truth #5: trauma and mental health are linked

trauma is a serious risk factor in the development of depression, anxiety, bipolar disorder, and other mental health conditions.

medications are commonly used to combat these conditions but medication only solves the symptoms, not the root issue.
.
.

text:
| ‚Äúand one day she discovered that she was fierce, strong, and full of fire, and that not even she could hold herself back because her passion burned brighter than her fears‚Äù
.
.
photography came to me in a season where it was much easier to focus on others‚Äô lives than it was to look at myself
.
.
a year ago, after growing impatient of waiting to photograph others i humorously summoned the courage to try some self-portraits. when i started to edit them,i cried. for the first time i saw myself. not as a bird with a broken wing but someone capable of capturing a moment, no matter how mundane, i was there just me and none of the baggage i feared i would never release. .
. 
so last night i went and did a sunset photoshoot. completely for me to take self-portraits and honestly i see the girl i didn‚Äôt ever believe i‚Äôd see again. i never was one to believe in the therapeutic properties of the arts but i can say that if you have a passion, follow it. no matter how ‚Äúoff-brand‚Äù it may feel. your soul knows what it needs. feed it and god will sow those seeds. üåø|
.
(sorry for making you read my novel üòÖ)

text:
this is #intersectionality.
childbirth is killing black women. 
3x the rate of anyone else.
black women aren't believed when they say they are in pain!

text:
the battles we often fight are for the message in front of us to be silenced because they mirror too much of our own pain. i believe many who discredit #christineblaseyford are terrified of her truth. it threatens their ability to keep a tight reign on the lives they‚Äôve built that help them feel secure. .
.
i was one of them. i was deeply engrained in my christianity. i was hopeful that one day i would feel whole. i used every mask possible to hide the deep uncertainty i had as a human being carrying years of trauma inside of my body. it took me 20+ years of therapy to finally take my life back, address years of sexual abuse  and also come out as gay. .
.
i share this because i know the opposing denial.  i know what it feels like to feel deeply threatened by someone else‚Äôs truth. even when, on some level you know they‚Äôre honest, you are terrified to agree, and believe you will have the support to sustain your own life. .
.
through the crashing and burning of many cycles, i‚Äôm grateful to be on the side of a ton of warriors for justice, humanity, equality. .
.
as we proceed i hope that this movement continues to be a megaphone for the broken hearts of so many that are terrified to express their own truths. i hope today, no one points the aimless blame at dr ford without questioning what it is about her bravery, beauty, and femininity that scares them. .
.
carry on, you amazing women. you‚Äôve converted this heart from being tangled in pain to set ablaze for truth and justice. üî•üî•üî• #ibelieveher because i can spot a warrior a mile away.

text:
i shared with you earlier this week about how i've been sitting with my feelings after  the most recent massively triggering events in the us exploded across social media. .

i'm done processing.  out of that inner work has come one of my most tender, vulnerable, f*cking unbreakable heart shares, in the form of a poem called "trigger warning". .

the name is fitting -  the poem contains reference to rape, sexual assault and suicide so if you are in a place right now where you need time to honor your own mental health, if you need to self care and process your own feelings before reading something like this, i honor that and i honor you. .

ultimately, writing this piece has brought me healing and clarity.  watching the women in my circle, online and in person, respond to dr. christine blasey ford and how she reclaimed her voice and spoke her truth has been powerful.  i see it in our eyes, how we see ourselves in her. .

to listen to an audio recording and read the blog, head to the link in my bio or visit www.goddesswands.com/trigger-warning

text:
it‚Äôs been almost a year since the #metoo movement exploded, and women around the world have been sharing their personal stories about #sexualabuse and misconduct in an attempt to change the way that our culture talks about sexual violence.

artist @themilajam jam wants you to take a closer look at what those experiences mean. the 29-year-old singer and actress has released her brand new ep bruised, which explores how violence hurts and changes women, before ultimately offering up a message of hope for the future. accompanying her new ep is a video for the title track, ‚Äúbruised," premiering on billboard today (oct. 4). in the stunning visual, jam paints a haunting portrait of the cycle of violence and abuse, specifically for transgender women of color, through painful imagery, violent scenes and even a specific angelic depiction of trans actress laverne cox. ‚Äúmany trans women are not allowed to come out of it on the other side without even being able to speak up about the abuse and the violence because girls are being murdered,‚Äù jam tells billboard. ‚Äúthis is just another layer to [the #metoo movement], where your voice isn't even being heard, and you're silenced because of death.‚Äù #milajam spoke with @billboard about including #transwomen in the #metoo movement, working with her friends @lavernecox cox and @mjrodriguez7, and why she has hope for the future. watch the video for "bruised" and check out the rest of the q&a at #billboard.com

text:
thank you to mercy medical center for their generous sponsorship and for serving on our planning committee. we appreciate all you do and are thankful to have you as a community partner! 
in 1999 mercy medical center established stark county‚Äôs first sexual assault nurse examiner (sane) program, which strives to ensure sexual assault victims are treated promptly by trained professionals in a safe, compassionate and confidential environment. in 2016, the program was rebranded haven (healing after violent encounters network) to represent its expanded scope of services to include all victims of violence. the haven team is available to provide medical forensic nursing care to individuals impacted by violence, elder abuse and neglect, domestic violence, human trafficking and sexual assault.

dedicated to excellence, devoted to healing since 1908
mercy medical center, a ministry of the sisters of charity health system, operates a 476-bed hospital serving stark, carroll, wayne, holmes and tuscarawas counties and parts of southeastern ohio. it has 620 members on its medical staff and employs 2,500 people.  mercy operates outpatient health centers in alliance, carroll county, jackson township, lake township, louisville, massillon, north canton, plain township and tuscarawas county. a catholic hospital, mercy medical center upholds the mission and philosophy of the sisters of charity of st. augustine and continues to be responsive to the needs of the community.
.
.
.
#tbtnstark #tbtn #takebackthenight #starkcounty #ohio #rapecrisis #advocacy #compass #domesticviolence #sexualassault #metoo #hope #healing #arts #canton #ohio #oh

text:
me too / medusa / open letter to men
i wiped the sweat of our lovemaking from my hairline where it was itching my scalp, walked out of your apartment into city lights books on columbus where i saw a postcard of medusa standing under an angry gray sky.
she was wearing red lipstick and smiling coyly, her hair a mass of wiry black snakes.
but this modern medusa didn‚Äôt look like a cave-dwelling beast of a creature‚Äîshe looked like me. she was beautiful.
medusa. born a beauty, coveted and raped by poseidon in the temple of athena, punished for her "transgression" and the desecration of athena‚Äôs sacred space via a beastly transformation, decapitated by a post-adolescent demigod named perseus in a game whose aim was to win rights to the body of the virgin teen queen andromeda.
do you see?
you vilify womxn. to protect ourselves, our dignity, we grow into your depiction of monstrosity. we‚Äôve teeth sprouting from our labia‚Äîvagina dentate. we‚Äôve hair curly with snakes, lips painted red with blood.
do you see?
we are this powerful deity. mercurial in nature, endless sources of fascination, a site for patriarchy‚Äôs projections of both fear and desire, symbols of rage and sexuality. and yes; maybe we are coming for you.
do you see?
i cannot be your ivory aphrodite, worshipped for my sexual modesty and ageless beauty or live my life eternally punished as streetwalker with a rosebush between my thighs. i cannot lay myself low, some contemporary version of shakespeare‚Äôs ophelia drowning in a your old bathwater.
like medusa, i, too, have cobras on the brain. but i don‚Äôt wish to turn you to stone with my gaze or wield the terrible power of my vengeance before me like a shield.
i would rather be tiresias, blind hermaphrodite prophet doomed to speak only truth‚Äîbut what good is truth in this place you've built?
what good is truth in a temple founded on lies?
#metoo
#medusa
#fuckkavanaugh 
#slaythepatriarchy
name: cole g√¶nn

text:
we are outside scotus because we #believesurvivors. because there is too much at stake. because we are on the right side of history. because we will be heard! 
can‚Äôt make it to dc? here‚Äôs what you can do. via @jesslivmo (who is outside scotus too!): i have said this 1million times but apparently y'all still haven't gotten it. call now: 
ak 
@lisamurkowski 202-224-6665  me
@senatorcollins 202-224-2523

nd
@senatorheitkamp 202 224-2043 (who just committed to voting no. call her & thank her). wv 
@sen_joemanchin 202-224-3954 ‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî if we don't believe we can win, we will not. when it feels dark is when we double down. worried we can't #stopkavanaugh? do something.

call your senator. 
go to a march.
message your friends and ask them to call. 
get to hart atrium if you are in dc. 
the *only* reason we are at the point we are now in this process is because of us. we built this moment and we must fight tooth and nail until it is over.  and it ain't over yet.

if mitch mcconnell had the votes, you better believe this would be done. and we know that a well places message from a constituent (ahem, #elevatorwomen) can change the process. 
nothing is a done deal until the end. and we have at least 24 hours to influence votes. so hop to it and fight like hell. #stopkavanaugh #cancelkavanaugh #believesurvivors #metoo #whatsatstake #keepshowingup #stayhuman
